explanation: The program was printing the duplicate count (number of later occurrences) instead of the number of distinct sticks. Since count = N - (number of distinct stick classes), the final print should output N - count. I fixed the last line accordingly (changing print(count) to print(N - count)).
fixed_code:
N = int(input())

Z = set()

count = 0
for i in range(N):
    S = input()
    if S in Z:
        count += 1
    Z.add(S)
    Z.add(S[::-1])

print(N - count)
